<dl id="n32055d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n32" href="#n32055d">N32 (VI.B.23)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n32all.htm#n32055d"> 55(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> scatterment</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">All the early Hindostani literature was in poetry, and this literary form of speech was named &ldquo;Rekhta&rdquo;, or &ldquo;<mark>scattered</mark>&rdquo;, from the way in which words borrowed from Persian were &ldquo;scattered&rdquo; through it. <small> &ldquo;HINDOSTANI&rdquo; <a name="EBHI" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBHI"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 479(b) [Hindostani as a Lingua Franca]</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
